#compdef tetro-tui
# =============================================================================
# tetro-tui — Strophox's "Terminal-based but modern tetromino-stacking
#              game that is customizable and cross-platform."  A
#              feature-rich terminal Tetris implementation built on
#              crossterm for cross-platform terminal rendering (works
#              identically on Linux/macOS/Windows).  tetro-tui
#              implements the canonical Tetris Guideline:
#                - Standard 10×20 playfield with 6-row buffer above
#                - 7-bag piece RNG (each "bag" contains all 7
#                  tetrominoes I/O/T/S/Z/L/J in random order)
#                - Super Rotation System (SRS) with wall-kick tables
#                - T-spin, S-spin, J-spin, L-spin detection
#                - Lock delay with reset on movement (15-move limit)
#                - Hold piece + next-queue (5-piece preview)
#                - DAS/ARR (Delayed Auto Shift / Auto Repeat Rate)
#                  configurable per-frame
#                - Soft drop + hard drop with line clears
#                - Tetris-like, Sprint (40 lines), Ultra (2-minute),
#                  Master (gravity 20G), Cheese (line clearing puzzle),
#                  Custom game modes
#                - Replay system (every input is recorded; replays
#                  saved as serde-encoded files for sharing)
#                - Customizable themes + colors via crossterm
#              Designed for tetris enthusiasts who want a modern
#              terminal-native experience without web/Electron
#              overhead.
#
# Author:  Strophox (https://github.com/Strophox) — independent
#          Rust developer who created tetro-tui in 2024 as a
#          personal tetris implementation.  Active maintainer with
#          regular releases.
# Source:  https://github.com/Strophox/tetro-tui
# CLI:     src/main.rs (uses clap 4 derive Parser + crossterm-rs/
#                        crossterm for the entire terminal-rendering
#                        + keyboard-event-handling stack)
# Library: crossterm-rs/crossterm
#          ("Cross platform terminal library rust" — Timon Post's
#           cross-platform Rust terminal-manipulation library;
#           ratatui R530's default backend; distinct from
#           termion R550 (Unix-only) by supporting BOTH Unix ANSI
#           AND Windows Console API natively.  The Rust parallel
#           to Go's gdamore/tcell R551 and TS-Node's cronvel/
#           terminal-kit R552.)
# License: MIT
# Status:  Active — 676+ stars on Strophox/tetro-tui; crossterm
#          itself is 4070+ stars on crossterm-rs/crossterm
#          (continuous development since 2017 by Timon Post and
#          100+ contributors).
#
